Welcome to yourCMDB!
=====================

http://www.yourcmdb.org
Contact: Michael Batz <michael@yourcmdb.org>



Update in short:
1.) Backup your yourCMDB etc directory and create a database dump
2.) Install the new version of yourCMDB
3.) Migrate the configuration files
4.) Migrate database structure


1.) Backup your yourCMDB etc directory and create a database dump
Create a backup of your existing yourCMDB etc directory and create a database
dump

2.) Install the new version of yourCMDB
Install the new version of yourCMDB using the INSTALL Guide

3.) Migrate the configuration files
Use the new configuration files as a basis and migrate your configuration changes 
from the old version.

4.) Migrate database structre
If you update from yourCMDB 0.3 or prior, use the sql/update.sql file for 
migration of the database.
